Reasoning: 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely category as the paper presents an experimental comparison of General Game Playing systems, which is a subfield of AI.
- cs.GT (Game Theory) is also likely as the paper compares the efficiency of different game playing systems.
- cs.LG (Learning) is a possibility as Ludii is a system that uses machine learning techniques to learn game rules and strategies.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possibility as the paper mentions a Game Description Language (GDL) propnet.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possibility as the paper evaluates the efficiency of different software systems.
